data.title: Cemil Cahit Toydemir
data.meta_description: Cemil Cahit Toydemir (1883; Constantinople (Istanbul) – July 15, 1956; Istanbul) was an officer of the Ottoman Army and the general of the Turkish Army. List of high-ranking commanders of the Turkish War of Independence List of Commanders of the First Army of Turkey List of General Commanders of...
data.text:
Commands held 53rd Regiment, 33rd Division (deputy), 4th Caucasian, 1st Caucasian Division

5th Caucasian, 10th Division, Inspector of the Thrace 1st Gendarmerie Area, 41st Division, 11th Division, Undersecretary of the Army of the Ministry of National Defence, V Corps, deputy president of the Military Supreme Court, General Commander of the Gendarmerie, XX Corps, president of the Military Supreme Court, First Army Preceded by

Fahrettin Altay Inspector of the First Army

December 17, 1933–June 15, 1946 Succeeded by

Salih Omurtak
